&lt;p&gt;Bolton Older Adults CMHT are recruiting a Band 5 Community Psychiatric Nurse to work on our physical health care team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will include supporting people under standard care with mental health needs who require periodical monitoring and support of their mental health and medication, including administration of Depot injections, regular physical health care assessments, side effect assessment and mental state examination. The role is supported by an Assistant Practitioner for physical health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is an opportunity for someone who is experienced in working with older adults with a range of mental health diagnoses, physical health co-morbidities and social circumstances; they must have a keen interest in promoting the physical health needs and wellbeing of service users within our care by following the Trust&#39;s physical health care agenda/ strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work closely with carers, families, the CMHT and partner agencies such as GP&#39;s and social services in order to achieve the best outcomes for this service user group.&lt;/p&gt;
